Design Thinking Registration - Voice Automation for General Store
Project Abstract
Domain: Retail Shop Management

Project Title: AI Voice-Based Inventory Management System for Indian General Stores

Problem Statement:
Small general stores in India face significant challenges in maintaining accurate inventory records due to manual processes, limited digital literacy, and time constraints. Traditional methods lead to stock mismanagement, expired products, and revenue losses.

Proposed Solution:
We are developing an AI-powered voice automation system that enables shopkeepers to manage their entire inventory through simple voice commands in regional languages. The system will:

Record stock entries and sales through voice input
Provide real-time inventory tracking and low-stock alerts
Generate automated purchase orders and sales reports
Support multilingual voice commands (Hindi, Gujarati, English)
Operate on basic smartphones with minimal training
Innovation:
This solution eliminates the need for complex software training and manual data entry, making digital inventory management accessible to semi-literate shopkeepers.

Expected Impact:
Reduce inventory losses by 40%, save 2-3 hours daily on record-keeping, and improve overall store profitability by 25-30%.




